A house fire which killed a doctor and four of her children may have been started by arsonists targeting a 'gangster-type' tenant who used to live at the property, neighbours believe.

Sabah Usmani, 44, and her children Hira, 12, Sohaib, 11, Muneeb, nine, and Rayyan, six, died on Monday after fire ripped through their home in Harlow, Essex.

Detectives are investigating the possibility that they were the victims of mistaken identity, and today nearby residents claimed that the culprits had probably targeted someone else.

