Mr Khaliq said: 'He had spoken at the mosque about how he would like to buy a house in the area.

'He planned to settle down in Harlow.'

Mr Khaliq said that he saw Dr Shakoor only hours before the blaze as they prayed at the Harlow Islamic Centre on Sunday evening.

He added: “That evening I was sitting and praying with him and his children.

'He was a regular at the mosque with his family who were always very well behaved.

'He shook my hand before he left. It is a complete mystery why this has happened.

'We pray five times a day and every time we are praying for him and his family.'

